## Description {#details}

A utility class to expose symbols from a static library.

If an instance of this class is attached to a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> as a fallback definition generator, then any symbol found in the archive will result in the containing object being added to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

Definition at line 269 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/executionutils-h">ExecutionUtils.h</a>.

### getImportedDynamicLibraries() {#a02e80f80933d19509377fe6a7114a38e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const std::set&lt; std::string &gt; &amp; llvm::orc::StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator::getImportedDynamicLibraries () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Returns a list of filenames of dynamic libraries that this archive has imported.

This class does not load these libraries by itself. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a> is responsible for making sure these libraries are available to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

DefinitionGenerators should override this method to insert new definitions into the parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

K specifies the kind of this lookup. JD specifies the target <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> being searched, and JDLookupFlags specifies whether the search should match against hidden symbols. Finally, Symbols describes the set of unresolved symbols and their associated lookup flags.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator &gt; &gt; llvm::orc::StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator::Create (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/objectlayer">ObjectLayer</a> &amp; L, std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorybuffer">MemoryBuffer</a> &gt; ArchiveBuffer, <a href="#a056835b41d568acaa2b5a15ec1a4a93b">VisitMembersFunction</a> VisitMembers=<a href="#a056835b41d568acaa2b5a15ec1a4a93b">VisitMembersFunction</a>(), <a href="#a1b5526b1881d5905911be2bc2ae1b74f">GetObjectFileInterface</a> GetObjFileInterface=<a href="#a1b5526b1881d5905911be2bc2ae1b74f">GetObjectFileInterface</a>())</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Try to create a StaticLibrarySearchGenerator from the given memory buffer.

This call will succeed if the buffer contains a valid archive, otherwise it will return an error.

This call will succeed if the buffer contains a valid static library or a <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/macho">MachO</a> universal binary containing a static library that is compatible with the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a>&#39;s triple. Otherwise it will return an error.

### Load() {#a703cd8845907b2859b4ebdd00c206bc1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator &gt; &gt; llvm::orc::StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator::Load (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/objectlayer">ObjectLayer</a> &amp; L, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> char &#42; FileName, <a href="#a056835b41d568acaa2b5a15ec1a4a93b">VisitMembersFunction</a> VisitMembers=<a href="#a056835b41d568acaa2b5a15ec1a4a93b">VisitMembersFunction</a>(), <a href="#a1b5526b1881d5905911be2bc2ae1b74f">GetObjectFileInterface</a> GetObjFileInterface=<a href="#a1b5526b1881d5905911be2bc2ae1b74f">GetObjectFileInterface</a>())</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Try to create a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/staticlibrarydefinitiongenerator">StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator</a> from the given path.

This call will succeed if the file at the given path is a static library or a <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/macho">MachO</a> universal binary containing a static library that is compatible with the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a>&#39;s triple. Otherwise it will return an error.
